               <msContents>
                  <summary>The <title>Tuḥfat al-Muʼminīn</title> (Gift of the Believers), a medical
                     anthology by Muḥammad Muʼmin Ḥusaynī (d. 1698) which he dedicated to his
                     patron, the Safavid ruler <persName role="dte"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/232859004" key="person_232859004">Shāh Sulaymān I
                        (b. 1648 r. 1666–1694)</persName>. The author aims to correct innaccuracies
                     found in the then-prevailing pharmacopoeia at that time, <title key="work_1161"
                        >Ik̲h̲tiyārāt-i Badīʿī</title>, and refers to several other medical works to
                     formulate his own. He divides the work into two major divisions: the first
                     entitled <title>Tashkhīṣ</title> consists of five chapters, and the second
                     part, <title>Dastūrāt</title>, contains three further subdivisions. A scribe
                     named <persName role="scr">Mīr Ḥusayn Shāh</persName> completed this manuscript
                     in <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001561" key="place_7001561"
                        >Lucknow</placeName> on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1796-05-28">21
                        Zī-al-Qa‘dah 1210 AH (28 May 1796 CE)</date>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_77-item1">
                     <author key="person_36318254" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/36318254/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ḥusaynī, Muḥammad Muʼmin,
                           d. 1698</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Tunukābunī Daylamī, Muḥammad
                           Muʼmin bin Mīr Muḥammad Zamān</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">حسيني، محمد مؤمن بن مير محمد زمان <addName
                              xml:lang="ar" type="nisbah">تنكابني ديلمي</addName>
                        </persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="dte" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/232859004" key="person_232859004">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Shāh Sulaymān I, b. 1648 r.
                           1666–1694</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">شاه سلیمان اول</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <editor role="scr">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" role="scr">Mīr Ḥusayn Shāh</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" role="scr">مير حسين شاه</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1072">Tuḥfat al-Muʼminīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_1072">تحفة المؤمنين</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmala"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> سبحانك اللهم يا قدوس و يا طبيب النفوس اتمم لنا انوار معرفتك
                        و اذقنا حلاوة مغفرتك شكر شيرين شربت حياة حكيمي را جل شأنه ...</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><!-- Check locus -->
                        <locus from="400a" to="400a"> برگ ۴۰۰ر (folio 400a):</locus> ببکوکی اسم ترکی
                        جزر است که بـه فـارسی زردک نامند. قد تم بحمد الله تعالی‌ ...دام اقـباله حـسن
                        تـحریر‌ یافت‌. </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa"> قد تم بحمد الله تعالی‌ ...دام اقـباله حـسن تـحریر‌
                        یافت </colophon>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa"> Completed by <persName role="scr">Mīr Ḥusayn
                           Shāh</persName> in <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001561" key="place_7001561"
                           >Lucknow</placeName> on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1796-05-28"
                           >21 Zī-al-Qa‘dah 1210 AH (28 May 1796 CE)</date>.</colophon>

                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>For three other copies of this work held in the Rylands, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7274"><idno>Persian
                              MS 77</idno></ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7067">569</ref>,
                        and <ref target="manuscript_26559">959</ref>. For a description of 238 other
                        manuscripts of this work, see FANKHĀ.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
